{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Scope correction while implementing: dropped the planned __main__.py signpost. The only commit_tree/update_ref in rebar_reconciler/__main__.py is the legacy-lock-file purge (_purge_committed_reconciler_locks), NOT the inbound-event batch commit. Anchoring a batch-write note there would misattribute. The accurate facts: _write_event_file (inbound_translate.py) writes inbound events without a per-event commit; the pass commits them in batch via git_adapter plumbing. Signposts land on the 3 files that actually matter: event_append.py, import_ndjson.py, inbound_translate.py, plus the canonical docs/architecture.md section."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783648061328436001,"uuid":"38b16aa9-a68c-49c3-b7b1-6084e9988cfc"}